demand: If you knew you only needed 2 out of 3 votes for an offer to be accepted, would you only offer 2 out of the 3 people good offers or would you split it evenly. Also to see if race affected what offer you made to people.
comment: Was a good experiment, was a bit long.

demand: To see how are decisions differed when placed in groups with altering proportions of different people.
comment: I enjoyed it but had to wait long periods of time.

demand: the experiment was about proving if the participants were actually left winged or right winged
comment: the experiment is very good in terms of allocating if the participants were left or right winged. the experiment can also be used to measure racism within the participants especially within the group stage.
Interesting to see what people would do when they have the power. People believe in equality when they have no money.

demand: How people decides to split their money
comment: It is a good way to see how people react and even if you have to wait most of the time, this is not too bad

demand: spread of money according to our political views.
comment: Seems more like a poker game as we were progressing in the experiment
Long and extremely boring, it could have been set out better.

demand: To see whether we judge and discriminate against others according to race, gender and political views.
comment: I felt it reflected a key issue however, the results may be more randomised as there were hints at the behaviour being observed

demand: Seeing how people would split a pot depending on their 'right' or 'left' preference
comment: Good and fun experiment, took abit too long

demand: About how selfish one can be when it comes to sharing with others.
comment: It was good, it was to check whether when there was no voting people would split the money just as they did before or would they be more selfish.

demand: The experiment was about whether people would be greedy for money and do we live in a fair world or do we live in a world where some many need to be poor where as other need to be rich
comment: i think it was interesting to see peoples decisions

demand: I think the experiment was about how much you value others and what if you're not monitored you'd do to give yourself more than others.
comment: I thought it was interesting to see what people put down, as many people put down similar amounts to give to eachother and then others were cruel with their splitting the money. but i thought it was strange that no one didn't give people less than about <a3>4 each which was nice

demand: How to share things equally and how others perceive this.
comment: Okay, takes time waiting for other participants

demand: it was a survey on general demographics and our views on political topics

comment: I thought this experiment was good as it was interesting to see how much money other people/participants also delegated. It was also easy.
